  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">NGO Support / Integrated river basin management at Koshi River</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The trans-boundary Koshi basin provides freshwater for livelihoods and ecosystem services for millions of poor people in Nepal and India. Due to the pressure from anthropogenic sources and climate change the stability of the system is under threat. The project purpose is to ensure pro-poor sustainable socio-economic and environmental development in Koshi basin based on the principles of Intergrated River Basin Management. The objective is to reduce vulnerability of people, biodiversity, and economic investments in the Koshi River basin caused by climate change and human activities.</narrative>
  </description>
